27/04/2005
ANKARA, Turkey -- Defence Minister Vecdi Gonul announced on Tuesday (26 April) that the Turkish government and the US firm Lockheed Martin have agreed on a $1.1 billion deal to modernise the country's fleet of F-16 jets. 
Under the contract, Lockheed Martin will upgrade 117 of the fighter jets, with an option to overhaul 100 more. 
Gonul said the deal proves bilateral ties with Washington are on track. 
(NTV, BBC News - 26/04/05)
